If you use MinIO, create any required root or access credential secrets manually, confirm the bucket creation behavior for your chart version, and review PVC sizing before installation.

## S3-compatible mode

For AWS S3 or another S3-compatible service, create buckets, lifecycle policies, encryption settings, IAM policies, and Kubernetes secrets outside of obsgen.

Update endpoints, regions, TLS settings, and secret wiring in the generated values before installing.

## Manual tasks before install

- Create object storage buckets or confirm that your storage chart creates them.
- Create Kubernetes secrets for object storage credentials.
- Review bucket retention, lifecycle, and deletion policies.
- Confirm that each chart version supports the values keys used here.
- Review network policies and service names for your cluster.
